## Section 8: Security (Mandatory)

```typescript
// ✅ REQUIRED: Runtime env validation
import { z } from 'zod';

const envSchema = z.object({
  DATABASE_URL: z.string().url(),
  NEXTAUTH_SECRET: z.string().min(32),
  NEXTAUTH_URL: z.string().url(),
  SMTP_PASSWORD: z.string().min(16),
  S3_SECRET_KEY: z.string().min(40),
});
export const env = envSchema.parse(process.env);
```

**Security checklist (ALL must pass):**
- No secrets in client-side code
- All user input validated with Zod
- SQL parameterized via Prisma ORM
- XSS protection via React + CSP headers
- CSRF protection via NextAuth
- Rate limiting on ALL API endpoints
- CORS properly configured
- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` unless sanitized
- File upload validation (type, size, content)
- Security headers (HSTS, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options)

